<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Db_Table_Row::toArray() do not camelize the field names.</p>

<p>For example, if a table has field named "my_property", it maps to the property "myProperty" of the Zend_Db_Table_Row object but the toArray() function returns it as spelled the field name not the property.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
class Foo extends Zend_Db_Table {}
$foo = new Foo;
$foo-&gt;myProperty = 'bar';
$data = $foo-&gt;toArray();
var_dump($data);
</code></pre>

<p>Actual result :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
// array
//   'id' =&gt; '1'
//   'my_property'  =&gt; 'bar'
</code></pre>

<p>Expected result :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
// array
//   'id' =&gt; '1'
//   'myProperty'  =&gt; 'bar'
</code></pre>

